==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spherograph
<hw>Spher"o*graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Sphere</ets> + <ets>-graph</ets>.]</ety> <def>An instrument
for facilitating the practical use of spherics in navigation and
astronomy, being constructed of two cardboards containing various
circles, and turning upon each other in such a manner that any possible
spherical triangle may be readily found, and the measures of the parts
read off by inspection.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spheroid</ent>⟦br⟧
